        "## QUESTION 1\n",
        "\n",
        "__Write an SQL query that pulls in the the salaries table and the collegeplaying table (and any other tables you might need) and store them in polars dataframes. In Python Polars, combine the dataframes to create a list of baseball players who attended BYU-Idaho. The new table should contain five columns: playerID, schoolID, salary, yearID and teamID associated with each salary.__\n",
        "\n",
        "For this question, I first read in the two tables and then joined them and filtered through them, giving me a list of all baseball players who attended BYU Idaho. I then filtered out the columns I wanted to view, giving me the final results for all players who attened BYUI in an easy to read table. "
      ],
      "id": "54717f00"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Include and execute your code here\n",
        "q = \"\"\"\n",
        "    SELECT * FROM salaries\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "salaries = pl.read_database(q, con)\n",
        "\n",
        "q = \"\"\"\n",
        "    SELECT * FROM collegeplaying\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "collegeplaying = pl.read_database(q, con)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Keep the most recent salary per player (by yearID) to avoid multiple rows per player\n",
        "salaries_latest = salaries.sort(\"yearID\", descending=True).unique(subset=[\"playerID\"])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Keep the most recent college record per player as well\n",
        "collegeplaying_recent = collegeplaying.sort(\"yearID\", descending=True).unique(subset=[\"playerID\"])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Join on playerID and filter for BYU-Idaho; ensure final rows are unique per playerID\n",
        "together = salaries_latest.join(collegeplaying_recent, on=\"playerID\", how=\"inner\")\n",
        "result = (\n",
        "    together\n",
        "    .filter(pl.col(\"schoolID\") == \"idbyuid\")\n",
        "    .select([\"playerID\", \"schoolID\", \"salary\", \"yearID\", \"teamID\"])\n",
        "    .unique(subset=[\"playerID\"])\n",
        ")\n",
        "print(result)"
      ],
