        "## QUESTION 2\n",
        "\n",
        "__Pick any two baseball teams and compare them using a metric of your choice (average salary, home runs, number of wins, etc). Be creative! Write an SQL query to read in the table(s) you need, then use polars to manipulate the data. Finally, make a graph using Lets-Plot to visualize the comparison. What do you learn?__\n",
        "\n",
        "I decided to see what the average attendance of a baseball game was for two teams, the New York Yankees and the Houton Astros. I thought that the teamsfranchises table would be helpful to call the teams their franchise names in the graph but I ended up not using it and just manipulaiting the graph details themselves. We can learn here that the astros typically have more fans attending their games."
      ],
      "id": "6c132bd0"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Include and execute your code here\n",
        "q = \"\"\"\n",
        " SELECT teamkey, games, attendance, yearkey \n",
        " FROM homegames\n",
        " WHERE yearkey > 1965\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "attendance = pl.read_database(q, con)\n",
        "q = \"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT franchNAME, franchID \n",
        "FROM teamsfranchises\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "franch = pl.read_database(q, con)\n",
        "result = attendance.join(franch, left_on=\"teamkey\", right_on=\"franchID\", how=\"left\")\n",
        "result = result.with_columns(one_game=(pl.col('attendance') / pl.col('games')).round(0)).filter(pl.col(\"teamkey\").is_in([\"HOU\", \"NYA\"]))\n",
        "\n",
        "(ggplot(result, aes(x=\"yearkey\", y=\"one_game\", color=\"teamkey\"))\n",
        "    + geom_line(size=1)\n",
        "    + scale_color_manual(values={\"NYA\": \"navy\", \"HOU\": \"orange\"})\n",
        "    + labs(\n",
        "        title=\"Average Game Attendance Since 1965\",\n",
        "        x=\"Year\",\n",
        "        y=\"Avg Attendance per Game\",\n",
        "        color=\"Team\"\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    + scale_x_continuous(format=\"{d}\")\n",
        ")"
